A few years after leaving Akwa Ibom Correctional Centre, a frontline politician, Hon. Friday Obonoh returned to the facility where he donated food and other materials in Uyo, theAkwaIbom State capital. It will be recalled that Hon. Obonoh was wrongfully ac­cused, framed and incarcerated in the same facility. He alleged that the politically orchestrated ordeal was to stop his bid for the localgovernmentchairmanship of Oruk-Anam The former councilor of Oruk-AnamLocalGovernment, visited the Akwa Ibom correc­tional centre during the week when he donated food materials tohundredsof inmatesand used theopportunity tothankNigeria Prison Service officials in Akwa Ibom for a job well done. -Advertisement- Heregretted thehugeneglect of the facility by the current ad­ministration in the State, saying the inmates are first human and wealth. Receiving the food materials on behalf of the Correctional Centre, the Assistant Comptrol­ler of Correction, Mr. Julius Ogu­erisaidthegestureshouldbeem­ulated by well-meaning citizens and corporate organisations of the Akwa Ibom State origin. While thanking Hon. Obonoh and his team, Ogueri made it clear that inmates are well behaved and are learning basic skills to make them meet the challenges of the outside world. While vowing not to leave any stone unturned in continu­ing to assist the Correctional Centre with other needs, he urged good-hearted Nigerians to join in adopting a prison project that is aimed at donating food, medical and humanitari­an needs to prisoners all over the country